events.name: San Antonio Spurs at Charlotte Hornets

headlines.description: — LaMelo Ball scored 16 of his 28 points in the fourth quarter and the Charlotte Hornets beat the San Antonio Spurs 124-120 on Friday night to end a six-game losing streak.
headlines.shortLinkText: LaMelo Ball has big 4th quarter, Hornets beat Spurs 124-120 to end 6-game losing streak

headlines.description: — Joel Embiid and Tyrese Maxey both scored over 30 points for the eighth time this season, leading the Philadelphia 76ers to a 124-109 win over the Orlando Magic on Friday night and breaking a 58-year-old franchise record.
headlines.shortLinkText: Embiid and Maxey each score over 30 points again to set 76ers record in 124-109 win over Magic

headlines.description: — The Denver Nuggets felt they let a winnable game slip away in the closing minutes during a narrow loss at Philadelphia earlier this week.
headlines.shortLinkText: Murray and Jokic help Nuggets hand Celtics their first loss at home this season, 102-100

headlines.description: — Dejounte Murray has tons of respect for Udonis Haslem. That said, he wanted to have the last word on Haslem's special night in Miami.
headlines.shortLinkText: Murray hits 3-pointer with 2 seconds left to lift Hawks past Heat, 109-108

events.name: Phoenix Suns at New Orleans Pelicans

headlines.description: — As Devin Booker hit his sixth 3-pointer of the night to eclipse the 50-point plateau, he turned and looked up about 15 rows behind the Phoenix Suns' bench, where his father and grandfather were sitting.
headlines.shortLinkText: Devin Booker scores 52 points, Suns rout Pelicans 123-109

events.name: Dallas Mavericks at Golden State Warriors
Indiana Pacers at Portland Trail Blazers

headlines.description: — Jerami Grant scored 37 points and the Portland Trail Blazers spoiled Pascal Siakam's debut with the Indiana Pacers with a 118-115 victory Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Grant scores 37 points and Trail Blazers down Pacers 118-115 to spoil Siakam's debut

events.name: Brooklyn Nets at Los Angeles Lakers

headlines.description: — Cam Thomas scored 33 points and the Brooklyn Nets beat the Los Angeles Lakers 130-112 on Friday night, pulling away in a dominant second half to snap a four-game losing streak and win for the fourth time in 18 games.
headlines.shortLinkText: Cam Thomas scores 33 points, Nets dominate 2nd half to rout Lakers 130-112
